CustomInfo: ConfigSection "Name=Connection timeouts"
CustomInfo: ConfigParam "Name=RobotToClientTimeoutInMins" "Parent=Connection timeouts" "Priority=Expert" "Type=double" "Desc=Time (in min.) before declaring a connection timeout for a client application. If the robot cannot successfully send data to MobilePlanner/MobileEyes during this interval, then the connection is closed. The minimum effective timeout interval is 5 seconds. A negative value to disable." "Value=10" "Min=-1"
CustomInfo: ConfigParam "Name=RobotToCentralServerTimeoutInMins" "Parent=Connection timeouts" "Priority=Expert" "Type=double" "Desc=Time (in min.) before declaring a connection timeout to the Fleet Manager. If the robot cannot successfully send data to Fleet Manager during this interval, then the connection is closed. The minimum effective timeout interval is 5 seconds. A negative value to disable." "Value=2" "Min=-1"
CustomInfo: ConfigParam "Name=RobotToCentralServerTimeoutInMins" "Parent=Connection timeouts" "Priority=Expert" "Type=double" "Desc=Time (in min.) before declaring a connection timeout to the Fleet Manager. If the robot cannot successfully send data to Fleet Manager during this interval, then the connection is closed. The minimum effective timeout interval is 5 seconds. A negative value to disable." "Value=2" "Min=-1"
CustomInfo: ConfigParam "Name=RobotFromCentralServerTimeoutInMins" "Parent=Connection timeouts" "Priority=Expert" "Type=double" "Desc=Time (in min.) before declaring a heartbeat timeout to the Fleet Manager. If the robot does not receive a heartbeat from the Fleet Manager during this interval, then the connection is closed. The minimum effective timeout interval is 5 seconds. A negative value to disable." "Value=2" "Min=-1"
CustomInfo: ConfigParam "Name=RobotFromCentralServerTimeoutInMins" "Parent=Connection timeouts" "Priority=Expert" "Type=double" "Desc=Time (in min.) before declaring a heartbeat timeout to the Fleet Manager. If the robot does not receive a heartbeat from the Fleet Manager during this interval, then the connection is closed. The minimum effective timeout interval is 5 seconds. A negative value to disable." "Value=2" "Min=-1"
CustomInfo: ConfigParam "Name=RobotFromCentralServerUdpTimeoutInMins" "Parent=Connection timeouts" "Priority=Expert" "Type=double" "Desc=Time (in min.) before declaring a UDP heartbeat timeout to the Fleet Manager. If the robot does not receive a UDP heartbeat from the Fleet Manager during this interval, then the connection is closed. The minimum effective timeout interval is 5 seconds. A negative value to disable." "Value=2" "Min=-1"
CustomInfo: ConfigParam "Name=RobotFromCentralServerUdpTimeoutInMins" "Parent=Connection timeouts" "Priority=Expert" "Type=double" "Desc=Time (in min.) before declaring a UDP heartbeat timeout to the Fleet Manager. If the robot does not receive a UDP heartbeat from the Fleet Manager during this interval, then the connection is closed. The minimum effective timeout interval is 5 seconds. A negative value to disable." "Value=2" "Min=-1"
CustomInfo: ConfigParam "Name=CentralServerToRobotTimeoutInMins" "Parent=Connection timeouts" "Priority=Expert" "Type=double" "Desc=Time (in min.) before declaring a connection timeout for a connected robot. If the Fleet Manager cannot successfully send data to the robot during this interval, then the connection is closed. The minimum effective timeout interval is 5 seconds. A negative value to disable." "Value=2" "Min=-1"
CustomInfo: ConfigParam "Name=CentralServerFromRobotTimeoutInMins" "Parent=Connection timeouts" "Priority=Expert" "Type=double" "Desc=Time (in min.) before declaring a heartbeat timeout to a connected robot. If the Fleet Manager does not receive a heartbeat from the robot during this interval, then the connection is closed. The minimum effective timeout interval is 5 seconds. A negative value to disable." "Value=2" "Min=-1"
CustomInfo: ConfigParam "Name=CentralServerFromRobotUdpTimeoutInMins" "Parent=Connection timeouts" "Priority=Expert" "Type=double" "Desc=Time (in min.) before declaring a UDP heartbeat timeout to a connected robot. If the Fleet Manager does not receive a UDP heartbeat from the robot during this interval, then the connection is closed. The minimum effective timeout interval is 5 seconds. A negative value to disable." "Value=2" "Min=-1"
